[2026-04-20 frontend] =<LinkTo class="btn primary">= rendered as
=<a>=, which hit the generic =a.btn { color: var(--muted) }= rule in
=app.css:823= and overrode =.btn.primary= on specificity. Muted text on
the accent background → fails contrast on indigo/dark themes. Fix:
explicit =a.btn.primary{:link,:visited,:hover,:active}= override
restoring =color: #fff=. Affects every =LinkTo= that uses
=btn primary= across the app, not just settings.profile.

