[2026-04-19] Sankey nodes (stub/scored/unscored/applied/interview/
offer/ghosted/rejected/withdrew/accepted/declined/no_application)
and sources-bar hostname rows are now clickable. They route to
=/job-posts?bucket|hostname|scored|stub=...= via new filter[...]
query params on =JobPostViewSet.list=:
- =filter[hostname]= (exact =(direct)= matches null/empty link)
- =filter[source]= / =filter[stub]= / =filter[scored]=
- =filter[bucket]= resolves to the same Status-name sets that drive
  the sankey, with =ghosted= additionally checking the 30-day
  staleness cutoff
=stub= threshold uses Length-approximation SQL-side; canonical
word-count definition still lives in
=application_flow._is_thin_description=.
=/reports/application-flow= is now public: anonymous visitors see
the global aggregate sankey (scope=all, user_id=None), Mine/Global
toggle hides when unauthed, clickthroughs bounce through auth guard
so no per-user data leaks. =Exclude stubs= checkbox added to the
filter bar.

