[2026-04-18] For job sites that block browser scraping (LinkedIn,
Greenhouse behind login). Backend: =POST /api/v1/scrapes/from-text/=
creates a Scrape with =job_content=<text>=, =status='pending'=, kicks
off the existing =parse_scrape= daemon. Frontend: =/job-posts/paste=
route with a textarea + Ctrl-A/C helper text, polls via the =pollable=
service, auto-navigates to the created JobPost. Cross-link in the
subnav between =/paste= and =/scrape= so users can switch approaches.
5 backend tests + lint clean.

* DONE Chat: "take me to that job-post" confuses score_id with job_post_id [ai]
CLOSED: [2026-04-23]
:PROPERTIES:
:ARCHIVE_TIME: 2026-04-23 Thu 19:33
:ARCHIVE_FILE: ~/Network/syncthing/Projects/career_caddy/todo.org
:ARCHIVE_OLPATH: Inbox
:ARCHIVE_CATEGORY: todo
:ARCHIVE_TODO: DONE
:END:
[2026-04-23 ai] =mcp_servers/chat_server.py::SYSTEM_PROMPT= gained a
new "ID types are NOT interchangeable" stanza under Page-Aware Data
Access. Teaches the agent that a score's id is not a job-post id,
requires resolving =score.job_post_id= via =get_scores= before
navigating, and explicitly warns against interpreting a 404 as
"deleted" when the likely cause is a cross-resource id mixup.
Covers the same class of bug for cover-letter/answer/question/
scrape ids as well.
[2026-04-18] Original report:
User asked for highest score, agent correctly reported
score 38 with a propose_actions button "Go to Score #38" (AG-UI working).
Then user said "take me to that job-post" — agent called
=get_job_posts(id=38)=, got nothing back, and replied "the job post may
have been deleted." Wrong: 38 is the SCORE id; the related job post is a
different id reachable via the score's =job_post_id= relationship.
Prompt fix: teach the agent that scores have a =job_post_id= relation
and it must resolve that before calling =get_job_posts(id=...)=. Likely
add a one-liner under "Page-Aware Data Access" or tighten the score
tools' descriptions.

