[2026-04-23] DevTools showed =/api/v1/scrapes/162/graph-trace/= and
=/api/v1/admin/graph-structure/= going to =careercaddy.online= (frontend)
instead of =api.careercaddy.online=. Cause: =routes/scrapes/graph.js=
and =routes/admin/scrape-graph.js= called raw =fetch('/api/v1/...')=
with bare paths, bypassing the Ember Data adapter that handles the
host swap. The frontend's Caddy then served =index.html= for the
unknown path and the SPA choked on HTML where it expected JSON.
Fix: new =api.url(path)= helper on the api service prepends
=config.APP.API_HOST=; both route files now go through it. Tests in
=tests/unit/services/api-test.js= cover the join, leading-slash
handling, host-trailing-slash trimming, and missing-host fallback.

