[2026-04-21 api+frontend] /career-data reworked end-to-end:
- Backend =/api/v1/career-data/= adds a typed =sections= array
  (resumes / qas / cover_letters) alongside the markdown =data= blob.
  Each item carries a stable DB id (=resume-39=, =qa-128=, =cl-77=).
- Frontend renders per-item sub-cards (CareerData::ResumeCards /
  QaCards / CoverLetterCards). No markdown regex-splitting.
- Subnav anchor-nav widget shows item-level labels as you scroll
  (resume title, truncated question, "Cover · <company>"). Fixed
  width so prev/next buttons stay on target.
- Subnav rendered inline per route (portal removed, no nested-dup
  hack); scroll-padding-top on html + .course-main so anchor jumps
  clear the sticky bar. Firefox-safe (portal timing was the bug).
- resume_markdown.j2 cleaned: single =## Name= heading, italic
  metadata line, h4 sub-headings per experience/project. Prompt
  fidelity strictly improved (the old 4-space indent had been
  rendering each resume as a code block for any markdown-aware
  consumer — see de2815d).

